===Pronunciation===
{Bl-uh-bur}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌbə(r)|-ʌbə(r)]]
===Noun===
'''blubber'''

#A fatty layer of [[adipose tissue]] found immediately beneath the [[epidermis]]. 
#[[Fatty]] [[tissue]].
#The thick coat of fat worn by many [[arctic]] animals, such as [[sea lion]]s, and [[antarctic]] animals, such as [[penguin]]s; used to insulate [[warmth]] in the animal's body.

===Verb===
'''blubber'''

#To make [[noise]]s while [[crying]].

